Present since mongocxx version 3.4.0 ([61ac563c|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-cxx-driver/commit/61ac563cd001afdc31906eaa0bdc9eefe86beeab#diff-34075b3734e196701572738898edfdf20383ceb771c46308a17dd7d50c770b8eR25-R28]). The Coverity issue was incorrectly diagnosed as a false positive on 2023-04-28.

{code:cpp}
{
  // Given a valid `server_descriptions` object...
  auto sds = ...;

  // ... default-initialized `_sds` and `_size` with indeterminate values
  // are swapped into `sds` within the move constructor.
  auto tmp = std::move(sds);

  // Undefined behavior: `_size` has an indeterminate value.
  assert (sds.size() == 0u);

  // Undefined behavior: `_sds` has an indeterminate value
  // when null-checked in the destructor.
}
{code}

Currently, you need to use the * or -> operators on a pool::entry to use the underlying client. So it is a little awkward to use when doing client operations (e.g. obtaining a database), e.g. [here|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-cxx-driver/blob/55c5b9e552b6fcb115a4db89a06e4aa3042b74a5/examples/mongocxx/pool.cpp#L48]:

{code}
auto coll = (*client)["test"][collection_names[static_cast<std::size_t>(j)]];
{code}

Perhaps instead, the pool::entry could also have an [] operator overload for obtaining the database?

